name: Iraq Babbler
rangeDescription: Southern türkiye, syria, iraq, and southwestern iran (reedbeds of tigris-euphrates valley)
description: Small babbler with a long tail and short wings, typical of other babblers. Warm buff overall with a pale throat and a lightly streaked back and crown.

name: Gorgeted Puffleg
rangeDescription: Serranía del pinche, southwestern cauca, colombia
description: Rare and endangered hummingbird found in the Andes of southwestern Colombia. Accessing its tiny known range is difficult, and only a few intrepid and lucky birders have seen one.

name: Northern Lapwing
rangeDescription: Palearctic; winters to northern africa, india, myanmar, and southern china
description: A handsome and striking large wader (shorebird) with long wispy crest. Fairly common in open habitats, from grassland and farmland to wetlands, and locally on coastal mudflats.

name: Gray Crow
rangeDescription: New guinea, including raja ampat islands (off western new guinea), yapen (cenderawasih bay, off northwestern new guinea), and d'entrecasteaux archipelago (off southeastern new guinea)
description: A large bird of lowland and foothill forest canopy, often near rivers. Somewhat variable plumage but has a long tail, bare, pink, facial skin and blue eyes.

name: Jackson's Spurfowl
rangeDescription: Montane forest of western and central kenya
description: Large, chunky brown francolin with a red bill, red legs, and bare red skin around the eye. Found in montane forest, forest edge, moorland, and grassland.

name: Long-crested Myna
rangeDescription: Forest of seram (southern moluccas)
description: A glossy-black starling with a unique, tall, permanently raised vertical crest. Also note the separate whitish markings on the sides of the breast and cheeks, and the pale skin around the eye.

name: Bornean Bulbul
rangeDescription: Highlands of northern borneo
description: Attractive and distinctive bulbul. Olive-yellow back, bright yellow throat and underparts, and black head with upright crest.

name: Socotra Bunting
rangeDescription: Densely vegetated rocky slopes of montane socotra; winters to lower elevations
description: Brownish bunting with boldly striped black-and-white head, bright chestnut wings and buffy wash on the breast that fades towards the vent. Endemic to Socotra, where it prefers rocky areas in shrubland and grassland.

name: Cuban Crow
rangeDescription: Cuba including isla de la juventud (isle of pines; south of western cuba), and southern bahamas (caicos islands)
description: A large, black gregarious species of open woodlands, palm savannahs, and human settlements (including agricultural areas and garbage dumps) near woodlands; often found in flocks of up to fifty birds. The similar Palm Crow has a much shorter bill with extensive feathering on top.

name: Eastern Plantain-eater
rangeDescription: Acacia savanna of central and east africa
description: Unusual gray turaco with a long tail and a bushy crest. White bars in the outer wing and white sides to the tail are conspicuous in floppy flight.

name: Bare-necked Fruitcrow
rangeDescription: Southern venezuela and the guianas to northern bolivia and amazonian brazil
description: Unusual medium-sized bird of forest canopy in Amazonia. Dark blue overall with bare, wrinkly blue skin on the neck and a pale bill.

name: Madagascar Partridge
rangeDescription: Madagascar; introduced réunion
description: Dark, chunky, medium-sized ground-dwelling bird. Distinctive male has a complex and beautiful pattern, while female is plainer and browner.

name: Garden Emerald
rangeDescription: Pacific slope of southwestern costa rica and panama; coiba and pearl islands
description: Small hummingbird with limited range. Male entirely glittering green with dark forked tail.

name: Rockwarbler
rangeDescription: Sandstone outcrops between hunter river and bega, coastal new south wales
description: Small terrestrial bird of Hawkesbury Sandstone region of southern New South Wales. Brown above, reddish brown below, with paler throat.

name: Lucifer Hummingbird
rangeDescription: Arid mountains of southwestern usa and northern mexico; winters to southern mexico
description: Small hummingbird with long, curved bill. Male dusky-greenish with contrasting white chest, expansive purple throat, and long forked tail (usually held closed in a point).

name: Norfolk Robin
rangeDescription: Norfolk island
description: Learn about Norfolk Robin: explore photos, sounds, and observations collected by birders around the world.

name: Brown-capped Tyrannulet
rangeDescription: Costa rica to western colombia, northwestern ecuador, and northwestern venezuela
description: Tiny short-tailed flycatcher. Yellow below with white eyebrow that wraps around the forehead.

name: Painted Honeyeater
rangeDescription: Eastern australia (roper river, northern territory to new south wales and central victoria)
description: Medium-sized, distinctive honeyeater of open woodland and shrubland in inland eastern Australia, where usually associated with mistletoe. Black above, white with a few stray streaks below, with red bill and extensive yellow patches in wing and tail.

name: Golden-crowned Manakin
rangeDescription: Eastern amazonian brazil (near headwaters of rio tapajós in southwestern pará)
description: Rare, range-restricted manakin found in a small area of eastern Amazonia. A small, mostly green manakin with yellower underparts; note the glossy yellowish crown in the male.

name: Scarlet-breasted Flowerpecker
rangeDescription: Southern vietnam, malay peninsula, sumatra, riau and lingga archipelagos, and borneo
description: The bright scarlet-red chest of the otherwise bumblebee-colored male glows in the gloom of the forest like a demon’s eye. Female is much more modestly-colored, with a gray head, a yellow breast, whitish flanks, and a dull brownish-yellow back.
